.TH BTH 8 "March 2025" "1.0.0" "BTH Manual"
.SH NAME
bth \- Bytes To Header Utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bth
.I -i <input>
.I -o <output>
.I -f <name>
[ -c <count> ]
[ -v ]
[ -s ]
[ -t ]
[ --ms-sys ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bth
is a utility that converts a binary file into a C/C++ header file containing a byte array.
It is useful for embedding raw binary data into C or C++ applications.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display this help and exit.
.TP
.B -V, --version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.B -i <input>
Specify the input file to be converted.
.TP
.B -o <output>
Specify the output header file.
.TP
.B -f <name>
Set the variable name for the generated byte array.
.TP
.B -c <count>
Number of bytes to read from the input file.
.TP
.B -v
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B -s
Enable silent mode (suppress non-error messages).
.TP
.B -t
Enable test mode (dry-run without writing output).
.TP
.B --ms-sys
Enable MS-SYS mode.

.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a file `input.txt` into a header file with an array named `result_name`, reading 10 bytes and enabling verbose output:
.PP
.EX
bth -i input.txt -o output.h -f result_name -c 10 -v
.EE

